<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="42" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="42">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubrecht, 1879" authorityName="Hubrecht" authorityYear="1879" class="Reptilia" family="Pythonidae" genus="Leiopython" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leiopython" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Leiopython Hubrecht, 1879</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="42" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Remarks:</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="42">
Recent studies revealed that 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Pythonidae" genus="Bothrochilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bothrochilus" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bothrochilus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubrecht, 1879" authorityName="Hubrecht" authorityYear="1879" class="Reptilia" family="Pythonidae" genus="Leiopython" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leiopython" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Leiopython</taxonomicName>
form a clade. Thus, since 
<bibRefCitation author="Rawlings, LH" journalOrPublisher="Biological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="25" pageNumber="54" pagination="603 - 619" title="Python phylogenetics: inference from morphology and mitochondrial DNA." volume="93" year="2008">Rawlings et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
considered both genera monotypic, they proposed &quot;the use of a single generic name (
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Pythonidae" genus="Bothrochilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bothrochilus" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bothrochilus</taxonomicName>
) for this species pair&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Rawlings, LH" journalOrPublisher="Biological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="25" pageNumber="54" pagination="603 - 619" title="Python phylogenetics: inference from morphology and mitochondrial DNA." volume="93" year="2008">Rawlings et al. 2008: 613</bibRefCitation>
). Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schleip, WD" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Herpetology" pageId="25" pageNumber="54" pagination="645 - 667" title="Revision of the Genus Leiopython Hubrecht 1879 (Serpentes: Pythonidae) with the redescription of taxa recently described by Hoser (2000) and the description of new species." volume="42" year="2008">Schleip (2008)</bibRefCitation>
demonstrated that this genus is not monotypic. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rawlings, LH" journalOrPublisher="Biological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="25" pageNumber="54" pagination="603 - 619" title="Python phylogenetics: inference from morphology and mitochondrial DNA." volume="93" year="2008">Rawlings et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
had used material from 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubrecht, 1879" authorityName="Hubrecht" authorityYear="1879" class="Reptilia" family="Pythonidae" genus="Leiopython" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leiopython hoserae" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hoserae">Leiopython hoserae</taxonomicName>
for their genetic analysis (GeneBank accession number U69835, Western Province, PNG at Mawatta). Until further molecular genetic data clarify the relationships of the taxa involved, and in deference to nomenclatural stability, we are reluctant to synonymize 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubrecht, 1879" authorityName="Hubrecht" authorityYear="1879" class="Reptilia" family="Pythonidae" genus="Leiopython" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leiopython" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Leiopython</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Pythonidae" genus="Bothrochilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bothrochilus" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bothrochilus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
